description.p:
1. A DNA of any one of the following (a) to (d):





(a) a DNA encoding the protein consisting of the amino acid sequence of any one of SEQ ID NOs:2, 4, 6, or 8;

(b) a DNA containing the coding region of the nucleotide sequence of any one of SEQ ID NOs:1, 3, 5, or 7;

(c) a DNA encoding a protein consisting of the amino acid sequence of any one of SEQ ID NOs:2, 4, 6, or 8, in which one or more amino acids are replaced, deleted, inserted, and/or added, the encoded protein being functionally equivalent to the protein consisting of the amino acid sequence of any one of SEQ ID NOs:2, 4, 6, or 8; and

(d) a DNA hybridizing under stringent conditions with a DNA consisting of the nucleotide sequence of any one of SEQ ID NOs:1, 3, 5, or 7, and encoding a protein functionally equivalent to the protein consisting of the amino acid sequence of any one of SEQ ID NOs:2, 4, 6, or 8.
